PURPOSE:
-------
To show the operation of Arp in a single subnet network.
To check with auto generated MAC Addresses using following logic:
For 6 byte MAC Address, first 8 bits is set to zero, next 32 bits is node id, next 8 bits is interface id.


SCENARIO:
---------

    1 6
  2     5
    3 4

MAC-PROTOCOL    802.3
ARP-ENABLED YES



RUN:
-------

Type '<QUALNET_HOME>/bin/qualnet default.config'.


DESCRIPTION OF THE FILES:
-------------------------
1. default.app -  specifies the application being used.
2. default.config - the QualNet configuration input file.
3. default.expected.stat - QualNet statistics collection
4. README - this file.
